                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.93./6–2849: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-06-28T14:00:00+08:00"
                            >June 28, 1949—2 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 28—8:18 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1391. ReDepeirtel June 22, 4 a. m. summarizing concise coherent manner position
                    US Embassy China and US policy possible recognition Chinese Communist Central
                    Government.</p>
                <p>Only one statement, however, not in accord Embassy’s understanding situation:
                    That is last sentence paragraph 2. So far as Embassy knows, only French and US
                    Governments have thus far decided maintain contact on diplomatic level with
                    Government at Chungking through secretary of Embassy. (See Embtel 1321, June 18
                    to Department, repeated Canton 549.) If Department has confirmation this
                    procedure from other governments, we would appreciate being informed.</p>
                <p>Sent Department; repeated Canton 587.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
